This paper is about dialogue systems, which are typically studied in the field of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically in the subfield of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training personalized dialogue agents using large-scale datasets, which is a common topic in the subfields of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves fine-tuning models and achieving state-of-the-art results, which are common topics in the subfields of information retrieval (IR) and software engineering (SD). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.SD are also possible sub-categories.
